<br>
The responses are to demonstrate that this is not the case...and if it was not the case then the class does not warrant a nerf.<br>
<br>
Facts:<br>
<br>
- It did indeed take over 10 hours to complete the deed, I believe it was either 16 or 18 hours.<br>
<br>
- The doors were not above level 2 in the upgrade scale.<br>
<br>
- Hibernian's relics were considered BUT they had upgraded their door and this thwarted this same tactic.<br>
<br>
- The same tactic had already been attempted on a Midgard relic...but the damage was noticed by shadowblade scouts and the doors were repaired and upgraded.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:<br>
<br>
This could have been prevented fairly painlessly by either an upgrade on the Albion doors or a patrol going by to check them sometime in the course of those 16-18 hours(understand though that Midgard forces were mobilized on purpose to help distract).<br>
<br>
Therefore:<br>
<br>
This theft was not easy to accomplish and in fact could have been easily prevented.<br>
<br>
If ye must find fault for a nerf it will be in the guards not noticing a battering ram not in our class abilities. <p><table width="436" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="2">
